<H3> <TI>   Government Expresses `Shock' Over Sarajevo Events </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702143694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service in 
English 1300 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has expressed shock at the Serb attack on 
the Bosnian capital, Sarajevo, which claimed 68 people and 
wounded over 200 others. In a statement issued in Islamabad, 
the Government of Pakistan urged the world community to punish 
those responsible and get the siege of the capital lifted. It 
has also asked the UN Security Council to lift the arms embargo 
against Bosnia to enable the Bosnians to defend themselves 
against the aggression. The statement says failure of the world 
community in taking any action would seriously undermine the 
credibility of the United Nations. 

