<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Economy Minister Meets Government Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802194994 Tehran IRNA in English 1818 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0802194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 8, IRNA -- The Islamic Republic of Iran 
and Turkey are studying export of Iran's natural gas to Europe 
through a pipeline via Turkish Territory. 
  Turkey is expected to import 5,000 million cubic meters of 
Iranian gas annually, and is also willing to go ahead with 
purchase of Iranian oil. 
  Turkish Minister of State for Economy, Cemil Erhan, and 
Iran's Oil Minister Gholam Reza Aqazadeh-Kho'i in a meeting in 
Tehran expressed satisfaction with consolidation of 
Tehran-Ankara relations. 
  The two officials referring to historical bonds between the 
two nations, called for expansion of cooperation in all areas. 
  Erhan and Aqazadeh agreed to follow up the accord through 
dispatch of a mission to Turkey from the Iranian Oil Ministry. 
  Erhan arrived in Tehran Monday [7 February] at the 
invitation 
of Minister of Heavy Industries, Mohammad Nejad-Hoseynian. 

</TEXT>

