<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yazdi: Human Rights Charges Aim To Discredit Nation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802201894 Tehran IRNA in English 2001 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0802201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tabriz (East Azarbaijan Province) Feb. 2., IRNA -- 
Head of the Judiciary Ayatollah Mohammad Yazdi said here today 
that the Iranian Government is ready and willing to offer every 
evidence to international organizations in demonstration of full 
respect to the human rights. 
  He said the foreign allegations of human rights abuses in 
Iran are unfounded and aimed only to disrepute Iran. 
  Yazdi observed that the primary duty of the judiciary is to 
ensure due implementation of the laws and investigate any 
instance of unstatutory conduct of the laws throughout the 
state. 

</TEXT>

