<H3> <TI>   Ministers Criticize Bhutto's `Propaganda Offensive' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0802114394 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0802114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The minister of state for home, Mr. P.M. Sayeed, has 
said that the Pakistani prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, is 
accusing India only to divert the people's attention from 
domestic problems. Speaking to newsmen at Thiruvananthapuram 
today, he said that Kashmir is an integral part of India and the 
government will initiate political process in the valley as soon 
as the law and order situation returns to normal. 
  Meanwhile, the minister of state for external affairs, Mr. 
Salman Khurshid, has criticized the Pakistani prime minister's 
propaganda offensive against India. 

