<H3> <TI>   Congress-I Demonstrates at Pakistan High Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0902140594 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0902140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Congress-I Seva Dal [volunteers group] workers today 
held a demonstration near the Pakistan High Commission in the 
capital protesting against Islamabad's interference in the 
internal affairs of India. Raising slogans against Pakistan and 
the United States, they burnt the effigy of Prime Minister 
Benazir Bhutto. Later, in a memorandum to the Pakistan High 
Commission, the demonstrators said Pakistan should stop abetting 
terrorism across the border. 

</TEXT>

