<H3> <TI>   Killing of BSP Leader Sparks Violence in Varanasi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0902014994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0035 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0902014994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Uttar Pradesh, all educational institutions in 
Varanasi have been closed down until tomorrow. Police and 
contingents of the Rapid Action Force are keeping a vigil in the 
city which witnessed violence on Monday. The chief minister, 
Mr. Mulayam Singh Yadav, has announced ex-gratia payment of 1 
lakh rupees each to the dependents of four persons who lost 
their lives in the violence. The incident followed the killing 
of a BSP [Bahujan Samaj Party] leader on Friday last. 
  The Congress-I president, Mr. P.V. Narasimha Rao, has 
deputed 
a team of senior Congress-I leaders to visit Varanasi for an 
on-the- spot study of the situation there. The team will meet 
the cross section of the people and inform the party president 
about the details of the incidents. According to a Congress-I 
spokesman, the team consists of the union minister of state for 
home affairs, Mr. P.M. Sayeed; the former Uttar Pradesh chief 
minister, Mr. Ram Naresh Yadav; Mr. Ramnath Shankar Shastri, MP; 
Mr. Harish Rawat, and Mr. Jain Mishra. 

</TEXT>

