<H3> <TI>   Minister Says 23 `Terrorists' Extradited to Egypt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0902142894 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0902142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi has stated that 23 
terrorists have been extradited to Egypt from a number of 
countries and that there are agreements on the extradition of 
criminals that the Interior Ministry has concluded with these 
countries. 
  The minister added that negotiations are continuing with 
some 
other countries to extradite terrorists who have fled there. He 
said that the Interior Ministry stresses that it is providing 
the necessary protection to anyone who gives information or 
statements that help expose any terrorist operations or leads to 
the arrest of terrorists. 
  Speaking at the opening of the exhibition of stolen items in 
the al-Jizah governorate today, al-Alfi said that the various 
police organs' training has been developed and their weapons 
modernized in order to confront the crimes and protect domestic 
security and stability. 

</TEXT>

