<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Efforts To Settle Bosnia Situation To Intensify </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0802161194 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1500 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0802161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Egypt's permanent UN envoy Dr. Nabil al-'Arabi has 
told our radio correspondent that Egypt, in its capacity as 
chairman of the Arab group at the United Nations for this month, 
will intensify its efforts and that of the other Arab and 
Islamic countries in order to find a settlement for the crisis 
in Bosnia. 
  He said that the Arab and Islamic countries have decided to 
intensify their efforts and do all they can to have the embargo 
on the sale of weapons to Bosnia lifted following the barbaric 
crimes committed by the Serbs in Bosnia. He added that UN 
Secretary General Dr. Butrus-Ghali is trying to persuade NATO to 
stage air strikes against the Serbs' positions in Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

