<H3> <TI>   Hamas Sets Dates for Strikes, `Confrontation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0802185794 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0802185794 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Resistance Movement, Hamas, has issued a 
statement in which it congratulated the masses of our Arab and 
Islamic nations on the occasion of the blessed month of Ramadan. 
It also urged the sons of our Palestinian Arab people to carry 
out the following activities: 
  1. To consider 9 February a day of comprehensive strike to 
mark the beginning of the 75th month of the blessed intifadah. 
  2. To consider 13 February a day of popular gatherings 
and seminars in protest of the ominous Gaza-Jericho agreement. 
  3. To consider 14-16 February days of confrontation 
against the enemy's forces and settlers. 
  4. To consider 17 February a day of comprehensive strike 
in solidarity with strugglers in the Zionist enemy's prisons. 
  5. To consider 27 February a day of a distinguished 
escalation against enemy forces and settlers on the anniversary 
of the great Badr battle [ancient Islamic battle]. 

</TEXT>

