<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Asad Said Using Hizballah as `Card' in Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0902113394 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 1030 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0902113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kafr Killa Voice of the South </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Uri Lubrani, coordinator of Lebanese affairs in the 
Israeli Government and head of the Israeli delegation to the 
negotiations with Lebanon, has stated that Syrian President 
Hafiz al-Asad is using Hizballah as a card in the negotiations 
with Israel. In giving Hizballah freedom of action in southern 
Lebanon, al-Asad wants to have a card to play in the 
negotiations. Lubrani said President al-Asad wants to make us 
pay to end this threat. 
  Lubrani warned that Israel will continue to strike on all 
occasions and with all means against Hizballah and other 
terrorist organizations. He indicated that any suspension of 
the talks with Syria and Lebanon would ultimately serve 
Hizballah. 

