<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protest Lodged Against Indian `Vilification Campaign' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0902105494 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1000 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0902105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has once again lodged a strong protest 
regarding India's vilification campaign against the Pakistani 
prime minister. The protest note was handed to the Indian high 
commissioner in Islamabad today. Briefing reporters, a Foreign 
Office spokesman referred to statements by the Indian president 
and by Salman Khurshid, minister of state for external affairs. 
He said that India cannot use such vilification to divert the 
world's attention from the atrocities being committed in 
occupied Kashmir. He said that such statements reflect India's 
helplessness in Kashmir, and give the impression that India has 
no alternative but to resort to a vilification campaign in 
defense of its policy of genocide. 
  When asked about the Kashmir visit by representatives of the 
European countries, the spokesman said the diplomatic 
representatives were not permitted to meet people freely. He 
said they should visit Sopor, Kupwara, and Bijbiara, where gross 
human rights violations are being committed. 

</TEXT>

