<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Curfew Hours Changed for Holy Month of Ramadan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902193194 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0902193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Interior and Local Authorities 
informs the citizens of the provinces of Algiers, Boumerdes, 
Blida, Medea, Tipaza, Ain Defla, Bouira, Djelfa, M'sila and 
Chlef, to which curfew applies, that on the occasion of the holy 
month of Ramadan of 1414 AH [1994], it has been decided to 
change the curfew times. The curfew will become in force from 
midnight to 0400. 

