<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Notes Mosque Attack, Bosnia, Other Topics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0902162094 Omdurman National Unity Radio in Arabic 1315 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0902162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman National Unity Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant General 'Umar al-Bashir, the president of 
the Republic, has condemned the 4 February incident in which a 
number of worshippers at the mosque of the Quarter One at 
al-Thawrah in Omdurman fell victim. He described the incident 
as strange to Sudanese society, particularly in view of the 
hideous nature of the crime. His Excellency did not rule out 
the involvement of foreign quarters, despite the fact that the 
statements of the criminals did not indicate this in the initial 
stage of the inquiry. During his meeting today with media 
leaders, al-Bashir commended the security organs for arresting 
the criminals and said the accused would be given a just trial 
immediately after the completion of investigations. He said 
Sudan's doors would remain open to anyone who wants to live with 
us in security and peace. 
  During his meeting today with media leaders, the president 
also said that decrees would be signed next week providing for 
the formation of the new states and the appointment of their 
governors, deputy governors and other members of their 
governments. He said in this connection that strong and 
trustworthy individuals with leadership capabilities would be 
chosen in accordance with the revolution's method of appointing 
political and executive leaders. 
  Lieutenant General al-Bashir also declared Sudan's readiness 
to send forces to preserve security and stability in Bosnia 
under the auspices of the United Nations. He appealed to 
Islamic states to send forces to put an end to the conspiracy 
being hatched against the Muslim Bosnian people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

