<H3> <TI>   Addresses Consultative Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0902215194 Khartoum SUNA in Arabic 1540 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0902215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 9 Feb (SUNA) -- Lieutenant General 'Umar 
al-Bashir, the president of the Republic, has said that Sudan 
will not give up its identity no matter how much pressures and 
statements against it multiply. He said Sudan's cultural plan 
required effort and patience and that Sudanese of various 
orientations did not differ on it. His Excellency explained at 
the first consultative [shura] meeting yesterday evening, which 
was attended by many scholars and thinkers, that the causes of 
the economic problems included the weakness of the inherited 
economic structure, external economic pressures, the continuing 
war in the south and the need to find more economic inputs. 
  Al-Bashir said the war in the south was aimed against Sudan 
and its identity. Rebel Garang wanted to abolish the Islamic 
shari'ah in the country. The peace would only come when the 
rebels came to realize that they would fail to achieve their 
overt and covert aims by means of war. 
  Al-Bashir said the fruits of consultation (?link) the ruler 
and the ruled and enable the ruler to [word indistinct] and 
(?manage) matters (?which) lead to consensus on important 
questions. 

</TEXT>

