<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   TNA Urges European Parliament To Stop `Interfering' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0902200594 Khartoum SUNA in French 1655 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0902200594 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 9 Feb (SUNA) -- The Transitional National 
Assembly, the parliament, has called on the European Parliament 
to stop interfering in the Sudan's internal affairs and to 
revise its attitude by obtaining firsthand information on the 
state of the country. The Sudanese parliament also called on 
the European Parliament to promote dialogue among the concerned 
parties in Sudan on the allegations made against Sudan by 
Western circles. In a communique issued in Khartoum on 
Wednesday, the Sudanese parliament cautioned against religious 
hatred, especially against Islam, calling on the European 
Parliament not to adopt politically motivated resolutions which 
could affect Sudan. The communique also condemned the plots 
against Sudan and the European Parliament's decision to suspend 
its assistance to Sudan under the Lome Convention. 

</TEXT>

