<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid To Sign Political Accord `Expeditiously' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0902193394 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1851 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0902193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 9 Feb (INA)--'Ali Salim al-Bid, Yemeni vice 
president and secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist Party, 
has announced he will expeditiously and finally sign the 
document of pledge and accord signed by the Yemeni parties 
recently. In press statements published in Aden, al-Bid said 
that by signing the document his party supports all the options 
of the Yemeni people. He called for Yemeni coherence for the 
sake of Yemen's unity and awakening. 
  Al-Bid accused some parties of trying to create an 
atmosphere 
that would prevent him from signing, adding that the signing 
will take place as soon as possible. He said what counts is not 
the signing of the document, but its implementation. 

</TEXT>

