<H3> <TI>   Importance of Signing Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0902211794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0902211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the Presidential 
Council, met in the economic and commercial capital, Aden, today 
with the brother representatives of the Shabwah Governorate 
expanded popular gathering, who briefed him on the results of 
the gathering held on 5 February under the slogan: "For the 
sake of a United and Effective Stand of the Governorate's Sons 
To Defend Unity, Democracy, Justice, and Social Development." 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid delivered a speech in which he 
welcomed the brother representatives of the popular gathering of 
the sons of the Shabwah Governorate and blessed the successes 
and results that the gathering has produced. He also 
congratulated them, as well as the masses of our Yemeni people 
on the arrival of the month of Ramadan. On this blessed 
occasion, he said, we wish you many happy returns, and we hope 
that this month will return to us while our country is in a good 
situation, God willing. 
  The Presidential Council vice chairman explained the 
importance of the accord document initialed in Aden. He said: 
We initialed the document. We will sign it expeditiously and 
finally and we will work along with all honorable people to 
implement and embody it on the ground and on the path of the 
homeland's progress toward a better future. He urged all the 
political parties and social figures and all good people to make 
the accord document a national program for themselves. He 
stressed that the Yemeni Socialist Party will be at the 
forefront of those who are working to implement the document. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid then stressed the importance of 
unity and cohesion among the sons of the Yemeni people from 
Sa'dah to al- Mahrah, as well as fighting the idea of division 
in the minds of the Yemenis, pointing out that popular 
gatherings in the governorates are the ones to which the 
document will go after being finally signed. He urged the sons 
of the Shabwah Governorate to be at the forefront of those who 
call for forming a broad front to glorify the document and 
comply with its contents. He blessed the efforts of the sons of 
the governorate to patch up differences and resolve the issues 
of revenge before the end of this year. Concluding, brother 
'Ali Salim al-Bid wished the Shabwah Governorate sons every 
success. the meeting was attended by Deputy Prime Minister 
Muhammad Haydarah Masdus and several officials. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

