<H3> <TI>   Guarantee Formulas Discussed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0902210394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0902210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Political Forces Dialogue Committee held a 
meeting in Sanaa today. The representatives of the parties to 
the dialogue committee took part in the meeting. The conferees 
resumed discussions and deliberations on one of the topics of 
agenda related to the implementation guarantees. A number of 
the committee members presented their opinions, proposals, and 
views that would produce the appropriate formula to achieve 
national consensus and to define the real bases of the 
guarantees of implementing the accord document following its 
signing in the Jordanian capital, Amman. 
  Following a length discussion, the committee members agreed 
to refer the various views and formulas presented by the 
representatives of the parties to the political dialogue to a 
mini-committee. This committee will review them as a first step 
in preparing a unified formula to (?endorse it) within the 
required guarantees in order to implement the document and to 
present it to the expanded meeting which the committee will hold 
on 10 February in order to endorse it and to discuss the rest of 
the topics on the committee's agenda. 

</TEXT>

