<H3> <TI>   Ugandan Plane Allowed To Leave; Cargo Seized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0902151394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1215 GMT 9 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0902151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Sanaa, Yemeni sources have declared that the 
Ugandan plane that had been forced to land in Yemen by Yemeni 
warplanes last Sunday has been allowed to take off for Uganda 
after the northern Yemeni Armed Forces seized its cargo, which 
belongs to the southern authorities. Military sources in Sanaa 
said the cargo includes, specifically, a large number of 
batteries and 15 telecommunications sets for military purposes. 
However, the Aden authorities insist the plane's cargo included 
nothing but equipment for civilian purposes. 

</TEXT>

