<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Arrives, Briefs King on Cairo Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1002102794 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1000 GMT 
10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1002102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Talks between His Majesty King Husayn and Yasir 
'Arafat, state of Palestine president, started in Amman today. 
His Royal Highness Crown Prince Hasan attended. 
  'Arafat arrived in Amman this morning on a short visit to 
Jordan during which he will brief His Majesty King Husayn on the 
details of the Palestinian-Israeli agreement reached in Cairo 
yesterday. He will also hold talks with his majesty on the 
latest developments in the peace process. 
  'Arafat was received at Queen Alia International Airport by 
Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, the prime minister; Dr. Jawad 
al-'Anani, minister of state for cabinet affairs and information 
minister; Dr. Fawwaz Abu-al-Ghanam, minister of state and acting 
minister of state for foreign affairs; and Dr. Fayiz 
al-Tarawinah, Jordan's ambassador in Washington and head of the 
Jordanian delegation to the peace talks. He was also received 
by al-Tayyib 'Abd-al-Rahim, state of Palestine ambassador in 
Amman and senior Embassy staff. 
  'Arafat is accompanied on his visit by Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, 
Ahmad Quray', Faysal al-Husayni, and Akram Haniyah. 

</TEXT>

