<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Pledges To Punish Bombing Suspects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0902150694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 9 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0902150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Salamah Hammad has received a 
flood of cables and telephone calls from various popular sectors 
and citizens, commending the rapid and effective measures the 
Ministry of Interior and security agencies have taken to 
apprehend the culprits who carried out explosions in two 
cinemas, one in Amman and the other in al-Zarqa'. The citizens 
denounced these criminal acts and demanded that deterrent 
punishment be meted out to the culprits. 
  For his part, the interior minister asserted that the 
Ministry of Interior and the security organizations, which are 
careful to safeguard this country's security, will be firm and 
punish whoever entertains the idea of undermining and weakening 
the security of this steadfast Arab country. He appealed to 
citizens to demonstrate further watchfulness and vigilance, and 
to cooperate with the security organizations whenever they find 
any suspicious object that could destabilize security in this 
steadfast and unyielding country. 

</TEXT>

