<H3> <TI>   Lower House Condemns Terrorist Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0902175594 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1700 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0902175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Lower House of Parliament has condemned the 
terrorist activities that Jordan is witnessing, and expressed 
their support to any measure the government takes to have a safe 
and secure Jordan. 
  In a statement issued by the House, the legislators praised 
the security forces' role in their efforts in guaranteeing the 
safety and security of the citizens. The condemnation came 
after the House was briefed by the Minister of Interior Mr. 
Salamah Hammad on the security situation in the country. The 
House called on all citizens to stand alert and united against 
any troublemakers. [passage omitted] 

