<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Queen Nur Offers Condolences on Basil al-Asad's Death </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0902184694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1615 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0902184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The first lady today received Her Majesty Queen Nur 
al-Husayn of Jordan; their Royal Highnesses Princess Basmah and 
Princess Haya; Ghayda' Talal, Prince Talal Bin-Muhammd's wife; 
Jami al-Majali; Jordanian Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam 
al-Majali's wife; and Nawzat Shakir, wife of Royal Court Chief 
al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir. She accepted their condolences on 
the homeland's loss of Staff Major Engineer Paratrooper Basil 
al-Asad. 
  The meeting was attended by the wives of the vice president, 
the prime minister, and the foreign minister, who also received 
and bade farewell to Her Majesty Queen Nur al-Husayn at the 
airport. 

</TEXT>

