<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Thanks Mubarak for Efforts in Accord Signing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0902222294 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 2200 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0902222294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sefi Handler] </F>
  [Text] Egyptian President Husni Mubarak telephoned Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin about 15 minutes ago. Rabin conveyed his 
appreciation for the efforts exerted in Cairo and his delight in 
seeing the end of the current stage of the negotiations with the 
Palestinians. Rabin voiced his appreciation for Mubarak and the 
other Egyptian figures who played a role in the mediation which 
culminated in a signed agreement. 
  Husni Mubarak invited the prime minister to Cairo. Rabin 
said he will gladly come, but he will wait for the formulation 
of the entire agreement to be completed. There is still much 
work to be done, the prime minister told Husni Mubarak. When 
the entire agreement is formulated and its implementation is 
launched, I will come to Cairo, he said. 

</TEXT>

