<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Shar' Meets Iranian, Pakistani Counterparts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0902192094 Damascus SANA in Arabic 1750 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0902192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 9 Feb (SANA)--Foreign Minister Faruq 
al-Shar' this evening received Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali 
Akbar Velayati on the sidelines of the consultative meeting held 
by the foreign ministers of the nonaligned states in Jakarta. 
The meeting was attended by Syria's ambassador in Jakarta 
'Abd-al-Salam 'Aqil and the Iranian ambassador in Jakarta. 
  Talks covered the peace process in light of the outcome of 
the Geneva summit, as well as bilateral relations. The two 
sides discussed issues on the agenda of the Nonaligned 
Movement's consultative meeting. 
  Faruq al-Shar' earlier met with Pakistani Foreign Minister 
Asaf Ahmad Ali in the presence of Syria's ambassador in Jakarta, 
'Abd-al-Salam 'Aqil. The two sides discussed bilateral 
relations and issues of common interest. 

</TEXT>

