<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Peres Initial Implementation Treaty in Cairo </TI></H3>
<H4>   Signing Ceremony Described </H4>
<F P=102> LD0902232294 Cairo MENA in English 2155 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0902232294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Feb 9 (MENA) -- President Husni Mubarak 
tonight attended the signing ceremony of the Cairo Agreement on 
implementation of steps related to checkpoints in the occupied 
Arab territories and the size of the West Bank town of Jericho 
as well as maps supplemented to the accord. 
  Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Foreign 
Minister Shim'on Peres initialled the treaty. 
  'Abu-'Ala' [Ahmad Quray'], head of the PLO economic 
department , and Uri Safir, Israeli Foreign Ministry 
director-general, also initialled the agreement's supplements 
and [word indistinct]. 
  Information Minister Safwat al-Sharif along with members of 
the Egyptian, Palestinian and Israeli delegations and two 
representatives of the Norwegian Government have officiated the 
signing ceremony. 
  Following the signing of the agreement, President Mubarak 
delivered a brief speech in which he alluded to intensive talks 
held here over three days. 
  He asserted that this agreement will remove all obstacles 
blocking the final signing by 'Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin on an agreement on implementation of the 
declaration of principles they signed in Washington in 
September. The president expressed hopes that upcoming 
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations would achieve progress. 
  He also congratulated both the Palestinian and Israeli 
peoples on the signing of this treaty, meant to put an end to 
bloody conflict and tension in the region. 
  Following the signing of the accord, President 'Arafat 
hugged 
President Mubarak amidst applaud by delegation members. Peres 
also embraced President Mubarak on the occasion of this historic 
moment. 
  The PLO chairman extended heart-felt thanks in the name of 
the Palestinian people and his name to President Mubarak for his 
efforts that helped produce such results. 
  'Arafat also thanked 'Amr Musa as well as Foreign Ministry 
experts for the help they gave in hammering out the treaty. 
[Word indistinct] consider what we have done over the past 
three days a vital step towards implementation of what we signed 
in Washington," added the PLO chairman. 
  Shim'on Peres made a brief speech thanking Presidents 
Mubarak 
and (?'Arafat) for efforts aimed at achieving peace in the 
Middle East. He also extended thanks for Foreign Minister Musa. 
  Peres said the talks tackled five or six points considered 
the most intricate. 
  I want to tell the Palestinians that we are serious and 
looking forward to peace between Jews and the Arabs, Peres said. 
  Attending were some 300 representatives of world media 
organs 
and news agencies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

