<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Agree on Resumption of Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1102191694 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1830 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1102191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1830 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The negotiations to finalize the security and 
civilian issues of the Gaza-Jericho agreement will resume on 
Monday, 14 February. At the same time, the talks between Israel 
and the PLO on economic issues will resume in Paris. This was 
decided today in a phone conversation between PLO leader Yasir 
'Arafat and Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres. The two men also 
decided to meet again in Cairo if the need arises to break 
through a stalemate in the talks. 
  Mr. Peres conferred today tete-a-tete with the prime 
minister. They were later joined by IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
commanders and senior Foreign Ministry officials. 
  Speaking to our political correspondent Gadi Sukenik, Mr. 
Peres said: We overcame mountains of tension and suspicion, and 
the negotiations with the Palestinians may now be held at a 
faster pace. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

