Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1202200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunis-7 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali today received the 
Palestinian president, Yasir 'Arafat at the Palace of Carthage. 
Yasir 'Arafat made the following statement after the audience: 
  [Begin 'Arafat recording] I held a good, positive and warm 
meeting with the president. I acquainted him with all that has 
recently been agreed upon in Cairo between us and the Israelis, 
and the agreement which we signed. On my arrival in Tunis I 
sent the president a copy of this agreement so that he would be 
totally informed of its details. I also pointed out to the 
president the significance of our continuing consultations and 
contacts so that we could reach a final agreement, which we 
expect at the end of this month, God willing. This would enable 
us to precisely and faithfully implement what we signed in 
Washington last year -- last September. 
  I listened to the advice and directives of the president, 
which I value highly. I thanked him, in my own name and in that 
of the Palestinian people, for all that Tunisia -- president, 
government and people -- gives to the Palestinian issue and to 
the Palestinian people. [end recording] 

