<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Faces `Major Problem' Ratifying Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1402110494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 13 Feb 94 pp 
1, 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM1402110494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ilyas Nasrallah: "'Arafat Faces Problem of </F>
Ratifying Agreement Inside Executive Committee"] 
  [Excerpts] Jerusalem -- Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat 
is facing a major problem vis-a-vis the ratification of the 
agreement he signed on 9 February with Israeli Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres on security arrangements for the Palestinian 
self-rule in Gaza and Jericho. 
  Apart from the popular opposition to the agreement inside 
the 
occupied territories, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT has learned that there 
is opposition within the Palestinian leadership in Tunis, as 
'Arafat's attempt to convene a meeting of the PLO Executive 
Committee to brief it and seek its approval of the agreement has 
failed. [passage omitted] 
  Palestinian sources have told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that three 
Executive Committee members -- namely, Sulayman al-Najjab 
(representative of the Palestinian People's Party), Yasir 'Amr 
(independent), and Samir Ghawshah (representative of the 
Palestinian Popular Struggle Front) -- refused to accept the 
invitation sent to them by 'Arafat to attend the committee's 
meeting to ratify the agreement -- which means there is no 
longer a sufficient quorum to endorse any decision in the 
highest executive authority inside the PLO. [passage omitted] 
  The refusal of al-Najjab, 'Amr, and Ghawshah to agree on the 
security arrangements means that 'Arafat will not be able to 
pass the agreement constitutionally at the Palestinian level, as 
the number of those who approve of it will not reach 12, the 
number required to complete the quorum. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

