<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Comments on Signing of `Final Deal' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1202175594 Paris AFP in English 1706 GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1202175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, Feb 12 (AFP) -- PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat said 
Saturday [12 February] he expects to sign a final deal with 
Israel by the end of the month to launch Palestinian self-rule 
in Gaza and Jericho, the Palestinian agency WAFA reported. 
  The PLO would continue its efforts to achieve a "precise and 
faithful implementation" of the September 13 autonomy deal, he 
said. 
  'Arafat spoke after briefing Tunisian President Zine El 
Abidine Ben Ali on the PLO-Israel security pact signed in Cairo 
on Wednesday, which overcame some of the obstacles to launching 
self rule. 
  Israel's withdrawal is due to be completed by April 13. 
  The two sides will resume talks in Egypt on Monday to 
finalize agreement on autonomy. 

</TEXT>

