<H3> <TI>   PLO Leaders, Opposition Analyze Cairo Agreement </TI></H3>
<H4>   DFLP: 'Arafat Signing `Illegitimate' </H4>
<F P=102> JN1202085594 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 12 Feb 94 p 29 </F>
<F P=103> JN1202085594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Taysir Khalid, member of the Political Bureau of the 
Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP], has 
emphasized that the front will continue to struggle alongside 
all Palestinian nationalist forces, organizations, and 
personalities against the Gaza-Jericho agreement and all forms 
of its implementation, including the Cairo agreement, signed by 
PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on 
Peres. 
  Khalid added that the signing of the Cairo agreement by 
Yasir 
'Arafat is illegitimate and is not binding on the PLO or the 
Palestinian people because 'Arafat did not refer to any of the 
PLO institutions that have a say on the present and future of 
the Palestinian people. 
  Khalid urged the PLO Executive Committee chairman to respect 
the Palestinian people's will, and to subject the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement to a referendum among the Palestinians inside and 
outside the occupied territories. He said this referendum would 
let the Palestinians express their opinion on this agreement and 
this destructive policy that furthers division within the PLO 
and the Palestinian people, sacrifices the Palestinian people's 
higher national interests, and changes the territories into 
protectorates under Israeli sovereignty. 

</TEXT>

