<H3> <TI>   PLO Leaders, Opposition Analyze Cairo Agreement </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hamas Spokesman Denounces Accord </H4>
<F P=102> JN1302094394 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 13 Feb 94 pp 28, 20 </F>
<F P=103> JN1302094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Tawfiq 'Abid] </F>
  [Excerpts] Engineer Ibrahim Ghawshah, official spokesman 
for the Islamic Resistance Movement, Hamas, has stated that the 
Cairo agreement reflects Zionist control of all matters and 
clearly shows what happens when agreements are signed in the 
absence of a balance of power. That's why we were not surprised 
at the Zionist military quarters' support and the preliminary 
Palestinian reaction of frustration and denuncation. 
  In an interview with AL-DUSTUR Ghawshah said: Anyone who 
reads the Cairo agreement will be angry and furious and will 
wonder how any Palestinian side could sign such an agreement? 
[passage omitted] 
  Ghawshah said: This agreement, which was overshadowed by the 
negative reactions of even 'Arafat and his entourage, will make 
the Palestinian people, after recovering from their shock and 
bitterness, forcefully support their basic constants of holding 
onto the Palestinian land and liberation, no matter the cost or 
the arduous road. 
  He added: It has become evident that the Zionist octopus, 
which clings to every inch of the occupied Palestinian soil, 
will give up this land only if a lethal blow is dealt to its 
head. [passage omitted] 
  On the new mediations between Hamas and Israel, Engineer 
Ghawshah said: Rabin has failed to solve or emerge from the 
security dilemma because five months after the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement, and 'Arafat's instructions to halt the intifadah and 
his promise to punish those who do not respond to these 
instructions, intifadah and jihad operations continue to take 
place and to daily constitute a slap on the face of Rabin's 
government . 
  Ghawshah said: The Rabin government sent many ranking 
military and influential people to hold a dialogue with some of 
the Hamas leaders who are in the Zionist jails. The reply of 
the imprisoned brothers was clear and categorical; the refusal 
to stop the intifadah and jihad operations. This is the stand 
by which Hamas abides, a stand rejecting any dialogue with the 
usurper Zionist enemy. All national and popular liberation 
movements abide by such a stand in their confrontation of 
occupation. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

