<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Source Denies Libyan Connection to Diplomat's Murder </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1402102794 Tripoli JANA in Arabic 0915 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1402102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli JANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tripoli, 14 Feb (JANA) -- An official source here 
today denied the French news agency's report that quoted a 
Jordanian official source as having said that Libya is the 
unspecified state which King Husayn referred to in connection 
with the Jordanian diplomat's assassination. 
  The source said: Such allegations which some Western 
information media have been circulating are totally untrue. He 
said: We are convinced that involving Libya's name in this seeks 
to harm Libya and, by the same token, to undermine the fraternal 
good relations that link it with fraternal Jordan. The source 
stressed that Libya has no connection with such actions which it 
condemns and rejects. 

</TEXT>

