<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister, Pakistani Envoy Meet, Discuss Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1002155694 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1002155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The special envoy of the prime minister, Mr. Asif 
Ali Zardari, had a meeting with the Iraqi prime minister, Mr. 
Ahmad Husayn Khudayyir, in Baghdad and discussed with him 
bilateral relations. He stressed the need to establish fruitful 
cooperation in various fields once the impediments are removed. 
The two leaders also discussed humanitarian issues of direct 
concern to the two countries, including the release of three 
Pakistanis undergoing imprisonment in Iraq. They also exchanged 
views on development problems in the Third World and underlined 
the need for South-South cooperation. 
  Mr. Asif Zardari conveyed to the Iraqi prime minister 
greetings of Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto and through him to 
the Iraqi people. He also conveyed goodwill feelings and 
humanitarian concern of the people of Pakistan for their 
brethren in Iraq. 
  The Iraqi prime minister recalled the close relations that 
Iraq traditionally enjoyed with the government and people of 
Pakistan and particularly expressed his high regard for Ms. 
Benazir Bhutto. He said she is held in the highest esteem both 
by the government and the people of Iraq. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

