<H3> <TI>   Regime Reportedly Arrests, Executes 20 Officers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1102195594 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1102195594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As part of the campaign to liquidate the officers 
who took part in the coup attempt in Tikrit in late July, 20 
senior officers in the Republican Guards were recently expelled 
and arrested. Some of these were even executed by the guards' 
intelligence organ, our sources in Baghdad said. 
  The families of the executed officers were notified by the 
authorities. However, the bodies were not handed over to them. 
Meanwhile, the authorities warned the families against 
publicizing the issue or holding memorial ceremonies for the 
deceased. 
  Panic prevailed among the Republican Guards as a result of 
this campaign. Many officers and soldiers escaped for fear of 
liquidation. 

</TEXT>

