<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Husayn, 'Arafat Discuss PLO-Israeli Negotiations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1002181694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1600 GMT 
10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1002181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn and Palestinian President 
Yasir 'Arafat held a meeting today attended by His Highness 
Crown Prince Hassan. A number of top officials from both sides 
attended. 
  The Palestinian president briefed His Majesty King Husayn on 
the outcome of the negotiations between the Palestinian and 
Israeli sides held in Cairo during the past few days. He 
explained the points on which the Palestinians and Israeli sides 
have agreed as well as the points that are still pending and 
need further discussion. 
  His Majesty King Husayn affirmed to the Palestinian 
president 
the importance of continued coordination and consultation 
because this coordination enables Arabs, particularly 
Palestinians, to restore their rights and reinforce their 
negotiating stand. 
  His Majesty King Husayn noted Jordan's constant stand based 
on supporting the Palestinian brothers in every way possible 
until they achieve their rights on their national soil and as 
part of an effort to alleviate the suffering of the kinsfolk 
under occupation. 
  Also attending the meeting were Dr.'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, 
the prime minister; Al-Sharif Zayd Bin-SHakir, chief of the 
Royal Court; Marwan al-Qasim, his majesty the king's political 
adviser; Dr. Khalid al-Karaki, his majesty's adviser; Dr. Jawad 
al-'Anani, minister of information; Dr. Fawwaz Abu-al-Ghanam, 
deputy minister of state for foreign affairs, Dr. Fayiz 
al-Tarawinah, Jordan's ambassador in Washington and head of the 
Jordanian negotiating delegation. 
  Attending on the Palestinian side were Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, 
head of the PLO Information Department; Ahmad Quray', head of 
the Economic Department; Akram Haniyah, President 'Arafat's 
special adviser; Faysal al-Husayni, head of the Palestinian 
negotiating team; and the Palestinian ambassador in Amman. 
  Afterwards, His Majesty King Husayn and Palestinian 
President 
Yasir 'Arafat held a closed meeting for some time. Following 
the meeting, his majesty the king and President 'Arafat 
responded to reporters' questions. 
  The Palestinian president left Amman this afternoon. His 
Majesty King Husayn and His Highness Crown Prince Hasan bade him 
farewell. Also present to bid him farewell were Dr. 
'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, the prime minister; al-Sharif Zayd 
Bin-Shakir, chief of the Royal Court; Marwan al-Qasim, his 
majesty the king's political adviser; Dr. Khalid al-Karaki, his 
majesty's adviser; the minister of information; the deputy 
minister of state for foreign affairs; Dr. Fayiz al-Tarawinah, 
Jordan's ambassador in Washington; and the Palestinian 
ambassador in Amman. 
  Upon bidding President 'Arafat farewell, His Majesty King 
Husayn made statements to reporters. He said: 
  [Begin Husayn recording] Through this short visit to his 
second homeland, His Excellency President 'Arafat provided us 
with a good opportunity to be briefed on what has taken place 
and, indeed, he did so. It was also an opportunity for me to 
affirm that our stand is constant in terms of fully supporting 
our kinsfolk and brothers in Palestine -- as he is the leader of 
their march -- to the best of our abilities during these 
circumstances and in the long run, God willing. I have noticed 
and I am pleased that our contacts are continuous and 
coordination between us is being upgraded to the level required 
to confront challenges and fully shoulder our responsibilities. 
[end recording] 
  Upon his departure from Amman, Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat made statements to reporters. He said: 
  [Begin 'Arafat recording] First of all, I would like to 
thank 
his majesty the king for his warm embracement of all our issues 
and problems. He also shoulders even our concerns. I would 
like to express my thanks and appreciation to you. Of course, 
this is not something strange coming from him. He is always 
shouldering the concerns of the one Jordanian-Palestinian 
family. We feel proud and are grateful to his majesty the king 
for shouldering this family's concerns in the face of all 
changes and developments. 
  I am pleased to be here today to put his majesty the king in 
the picture on developments and the talks I held with Peres, as 
well as talks between the Israeli delegation and the Palestinian 
delegation. I presented to his majesty the king the official 
documents that were signed. Moreover, I listened to his good 
views and ideas on confronting all future issues which we should 
address through joint efforts and action. This 
Jordanian-Palestinian family is a united family under his 
majesty the king's continuous care, God willing. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

