<H3> <TI>   `Official' Source: Libya Behind Diplomat's Murder </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1302203394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 2000 GMT 13 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1302203394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Randah Habib from Amman from the "Panorama" </F>
program] 
  [Excerpt] Jordan's King Husayn has said that the killers of 
the Jordanian diplomat in Beirut, at the end of last month, 
belong to an extremist group that received orders from an Arab 
country. The king did not disclose the name of that country. 
An official Jordanian source, however, told our radio that the 
Arab country is Libya and that the group, which carried out the 
operation, is Fatah-the Revolutionary Council led by Abu-Nida. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

