<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iran Reportedly Urges House To Stop Gaza-Jericho </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1102205094 Amman SHIHAN in Arabic 12-18 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> JN1102205094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SHIHAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] SHIHAN has learned that House of Representatives 
Speaker Tahir al-Masri has received a letter from Iranian Majles 
Speaker 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri. 
  SHIHAN has obtained the text of the letter, which urges the 
Jordanian House of Representatives to adopt appropriate measures 
to nullify the Gaza-Jericho agreement, dubbed by the letter as a 
disgraceful treaty. 
  The letter asserted that a practical approach to nullify the 
agreement is to emphasize armed jihad as the only and best way 
to face Zionist schemes and colonialism. 
  The letter explained Iran's view toward threats to the 
al-Aqsa Mosque in holy Jerusalem. The letter denounced the 
Islamic nations' silence toward the serious, false decisions 
made by what it termed the demonic Zionist movement against the 
al-Aqsa Mosque. 

</TEXT>

