<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Affirms Stance on Palestinian State, Comments </TI></H3>
<H4>   Notes `Palestinian Entity' </H4>
<F P=102> TA1002173294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 10 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1002173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin has said that although 
terror hurts, we must once and for all solve the conflict. The 
weapon of terror is in the hands of those who oppose us. Today, 
we are in control of the territories, yet we are unable to foil 
terrorism. If our partner realizes that security is important 
to us, and if he understands that he will not attain his goals 
as long as there is no full security, he will have an interest 
in seeing to it that security is realized. 
  Mr. Rabin further said that he recognizes the existence of a 
Palestinian entity, but distinguishes between it and a state. 
The Palestinians will have their flag and other symbols, such 
as a police force. They are entitled to have symbols, Rabin 
told the Labor Party Bureau in Tel Aviv today. 

</TEXT>

