<H3> <TI>   Valley Settlers Set Up Armed Guard </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1002174794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 10 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1002174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Jewish settlers of the Jordan Rift Valley have 
set up an armed guard which will patrol the roads of the region. 
They have presented the government with their red lines for the 
next stages of the political process. Our correspondent Gil 
Litman reports that the Jordan Valley settlers held an emergency 
meeting this afternoon, in reaction to the signing of the Cairo 
agreement. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1400 GMT on 10 February 
adds the following: "In their meeting today, the settlers 
decided to present the three no's they will not allow to be 
broken: no Palestinian self-rule in the Jordan Rift Valley; no 
armed Palestinian police; and no territorial corridors for the 
Palestinians in the valley."] 
  David Levi, chairman of the regional council, claims that 
since the Document of Principles has been signed in Washington, 
Arabs have been illegally building in several locations in the 
region. He called these deliberate Arab settlements. 

