<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   ICO Secretary General Stops Over for Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Comments on India, Kashmir </H4>
<F P=102> BK0902160094 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0902160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Hamid al-Ghabid, secretary general of the 
Islamic Conference Organization [ICO], urged India to revise its 
inhuman policy on occupied Kashmir and adopt a path for the 
peaceful resolution of the Jammu and Kashmir dispute in 
accordance with the UN resolutions. In a statement on arrival 
in Islamabad today on a two-day visit to Pakistan, he said the 
legitimate aspirations of the Kashmiri people cannot be crushed 
by force. The ICO secretary general said the Indian atrocities 
have crossed the limits on which the ICO is deeply concerned. 
The large-scale massacres in Sopor and Kupwara, in which 
hundreds of people were martyred, have dealt a deep blow to the 
Islamic world. He said the ICO will move a resolution at the UN 
Human Rights Commission meeting currently being held in Geneva 
to halt the human rights violations in occupied Kashmir. 
  On Bosnia-Herzegovina, the secretary general said our 
efforts 
are to get the use of force against Serbs authorized by the UN 
Security Council and also get the unjust and illegitimate arms 
embargo on Bosnia-Herzegovina Government lifted. 

</TEXT>

