<H3> <TI>   Government Captures Four Posts; Rebels Bombard Kabul </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1002171894 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Dari 1600 
GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1002171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dari </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a report by a BAKHTAR military 
correspondent, as a result of the attack by forces of the 
Islamic army, four enemy posts have been captured in the 
direction of Chehelsotun by units of the Islamic army. [words 
indistinct] were killed in Jangalak and around Bala Hesar and a 
number of others were injured. To compensate for their repeated 
defeats, the infamous militia today targeted residential areas 
of Kabul City with savage rocket attacks. As a result a number 
of our innocent compatriots were killed or injured. In addition 
to the loss of lives, the landing of rockets caused much 
material damage too. The artillery of the Islamic army 
responded to the savage rocket attack of the infamous militia by 
crushing the enemy positions in Maranjan hill and Charasiab with 
heavy weapons fire. As a result extensive loss of life and 
heavy damage were inflicted on the infamous militia. According 
to another report, this morning an aeroplane of Dostam's militia 
stealthily bombarded residential areas of the city. Fortunately, 
it caused no loss of life, but much damage was inflicted on 
residential areas. 

</TEXT>

