<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabbani `Conditionally' Accepts ICO Cease-Fire Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1102184294 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1530 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1102184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Borhanoddin Rabbani, president of Afghanistan, has 
conditionally accepted the proposal of Islamic Conference 
Organization [ICO] Secretary General Hamid al-Ghabid to 
establish a cease-fire. During a two-day visit to Pakistan, 
Algabid meet with met representatives of the warring sides in 
Afghanistan and proposed that a cease-fire be observed during 
the blessed month of Ramadan. 
  Borhanoddin Rabbani has said that he will accept a 
cease-fire 
with Hekmatyar's Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party] on the condition 
that the Hezb-e Eslami pledges to observe it as well. 
  In the meantime, reports from Afghanistan suggest that the 
two sides' planes subjected one another's positions to aerial 
bombardment today. On the basis of these reports, heavy weapons 
fire was exchanged between the warring sides today in several 
parts of Kabul. 

</TEXT>

