<H3> <TI>   Warring Sides Deny Official Cease-Fire in Effect </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1302185794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1302185794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Reports from Kabul suggest that an unofficial 
cease-fire has come into effect there. This is at a time when 
the residents of Kabul face growing problems in connection with 
obtaining food. 
  In the meantime, the warring sides in Afghanistan have 
rejected rumors that an official cease-fire has been announced 
in Kabul. One official from Rabbani's faction said: The current 
cease-fire is a result of bad weather, snow, and the month of 
Ramadan and it is not, in any way, an official cease-fire. 

</TEXT>

