<H3> <TI>   Hekmatyar Appeals to Iran To Take Active Peace Role </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1302135594 Tehran IRNA in English 1328 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1302135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 13, IRNA -- Afghan Prime Minister 
Golboddin Hekmatyar appealed to Iran to take an active role for 
restoration of peace in Afghanistan. 
  In a telephone conversation with Iran's Minister of Foreign 
Affairs, 'Ali Akbar Velayati, he appreciated Iran's former peace 
efforts in his country. 
  Hekmatyar congratulated Velayati on the anniversary of the 
triumph of the Islamic Revolution and on the beginning of the 
holy month of Ramadan. 
  Velayati in response expressed concern over the current 
fighting in Afghanistan and voiced Iran's readiness to resolve 
the conflict. 
  Since the outbreak of the civil war in Afghanistan, the 
Islamic Republic of Iran has repeatedly called on the 
belligerent parties to end the conflict and has launched 
mediation efforts to this end. 

</TEXT>

