<H3> <TI>   New Director General Appointed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1302112294 Tehran IRNA in English 1022 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1302112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 13, IRNA -- Leader of the Islamic 
Revolution Ayatollah 'Ali Khamene'i appointed 'Ali Larijani to 
the post of director general of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
Broadcasting (IRIB) here Sunday. 
  The appointment was made for a period of five years. 
Larijani was also appointed as the member of the High Council 
of the Cultural Revolution. 
  Larijani who, prior to his new assingment served as the 
minister of culture and islamic guidance, replaces Mohammad 
Hashemi who run IRIB for 13 years. 

</TEXT>

