<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee To Sign Accord in Amman 20 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1102203594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1102203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', 
brother Ahmad Jabir 'Afif, rapporteur of the Political Forces 
Dialogue Committee, explained that the committee last night 
concluded its discussions and approval of issues pertaining to 
the constitutional, legal, and procedural guarantees concerning 
the signing of the accord document in the Jordanian capital, 
Amman. 
  Brother Ahmad Jabir 'Afif indicated that based on an 
agreement with the brothers in the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan, 
it has been decided to set 10 Ramadan, corresponding to 20 
February, as the date for signing the agreement. 
  At the conclusion of his statement, brother Ahmad Jabir 
'Afif 
extended the Political Forces Dialogue Committee's 
congratulations to our Yemeni people and all peoples of Arab and 
Islamic nations on the beginning of the blessed month of Ramadan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

