<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Draft Labor Law Prepared After PLO Request </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1202114994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1011 GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1202114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 12 Feb (MENA)--The Arab Labor Organization 
[ALO] has prepared a draft Palestinian labor law that has been 
revised by a joint committee made up of experts from the ALO and 
the PLO, which requested the law. 
  Announcing this, ALO Director General Bakr Muhammad Rasul 
said the draft law was based on the main principles stipulated 
in Arab and international labor standards, taking into 
consideration the Palestinian people's general circumstances and 
the establishment of a Palestinian state. 
  He explained that the Palestinian draft law has 11 sections. 
Each section contains several chapters and articles about 
idioms, definitions, and general rules on employment, individual 
work contracts, working and rest hours, leaves, wages, 
juvenile's and women's labor, settling collective labor 
disputes, collective negotiations, collective work contracts, 
and inspection. 

</TEXT>

