<H3> <TI>   Velayati Appoints First Deputy Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1402140294 Tehran IRNA in English 1323 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1402140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 14, IRNA -- Iran's Foreign Minister 
'Ali Akbar Velayati here Monday appointed Mohammad Hashemi as 
his first deputy. Hashemi has served as head of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran Broadcasting (IRIB) for the past 13 years. 
  In a decree on Sunday, leader of the Islamic revolution 
Ayatollah 'Ali Khamene'i appointed former Islamic Guidance 
Minister 'Ali Larijani as the new IRIB head. 

