<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Appoints New Islamic Guidance Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502074794 Tehran IRNA in English 0642 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1502074794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 15, IRNA -- President Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani in a letter to Majles speaker here Tuesday 
introduced Mostafa Mirsalim as the new minister of culture and 
islamic guidance. 
  The proposal is in compliance with Article 133 of the 
constitution of the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  Mirsalim replaces 'Ali Larijani who last Sunday was 
appointed 
by leader of the islamic revolution as the new head of the 
Islamic Republic of Iran Broadcasting (IRIB). 
  Born in 1947, Mirsalim received his post-graduate degree in 
mechanics in Paris in 1972. 
  He was an active member of the Islamic association of 
Iranian 
students both at home and abroad for which he was arrested and 
imprisoned several times by security forces. 
  Mirsalim has previously served in various state posts such 
as 
first deputy interior minister, supreme presidential advisor, 
member of the high council of cultural revolution as well as the 
council's secretary. 
  He is married and has three children. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

