<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Consulate in Lahore Denies Involvement With Shooting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1402070094 Tehran IRNA in English 0514 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1402070094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad, Tehran, Feb. 14, IRNA -- The Iranian 
consulate in Lahore denied any involvement of the Iranian 
diplomats in the shooting at the leaders of the Wahhabi Sahabeh 
Corps in the city. 
  In a press release 13 February, the consulate said that the 
charges leveled in the complaint of a particular group against 
the Iranian diplomats were totally baseless and unfounded. 
  It also added, "Iran is against any kind of interference in 
the internal affairs of other countries." 
  Two leaders of the Wahhabi Sahabeh corps were shot and 
wounded by unidentified persons in Lahore Friday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

