<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Aircraft Launch 2 Raids on Iqlim al-Tuffah </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1502094094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0900 GMT 15 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1502094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israeli warplanes carried out a raid on Mlita hill 
in Iqlim al-Tuffah at 1000 today. One of the planes fired four 
missiles at the target. The planes continued to fly low over 
the area until 1010, drawing antiaircraft fire from Lebanese 
Army positions. At 1030, Israeli aircraft again raided Iqlim 
al-Tuffah. 
  Israeli military aircraft flew over al-Nabatiyah and Iqlim 
al-Tuffah at 0930 today, staging mock raids. The military 
aircraft were accompanied by an Israeli MK reconnaissance plane. 

</TEXT>

