<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buwayz Receives Christopher's Message on Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1402185394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 14 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1402185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lebanese officials are watching with keen 
interest this week's developments. After the resumption today 
of the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations in Taba to work out the 
final details of the Israeli military withdrawal from Gaza and 
Jericho and the transfer of civilian power, and on the eve of 
the bilateral negotiations in Washington, U.S. Ambassador to 
Lebanon Mark Hambley delivered to Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz 
a written message from U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher. 
  The ambassador would not reveal the contents of the message, 
saying only that it deals with the bilateral peace talks that 
will resume in Washington tomorrow. Hambley expressed optimism 
about the results of the talks. He said the deliberate tension 
and violence in southern Lebanon is aimed at undermining the 
talks. He stressed that his country is eager to maintain the 
peacekeeping forces in the south as a factor of stability in 
Lebanon. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

