<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Hirawi on Israeli Withdrawal, Resistance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1402204794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 2000 GMT 14 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1402204794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Ilyas al-Hirawi has stressed that Lebanon 
wants land in return for peace and wants sovereignty over its 
territory in return for peace. He said resistance is a result, 
not a cause of the Israeli occupation, and Israel's withdrawal 
will return things to their old situation. President al-Hirawi 
reiterated that there can be no just and comprehensive peace 
before liberating the south and Western al-Biqa', because this 
is the will of all Lebanese. 
  President al-Hirawi was speaking at an iftar [fast-breaking] 
banquet hosted by Mrs. Randa Birri, head of the Lebanese 
Handicapped Society at the Summerland Hotel. The iftar was 
attended by Chamber of Deputies Speaker Nabih Birri, Prime 
Minister Rafiq al-Hariri, and a number of ministers, deputies, 
and foreign diplomats. 

</TEXT>

