and loyalty in carrying out its noble mission. 
  He said the prime minister was briefed on the public 
security 
situation in the Kingdom and the qualitative training activities 
implemented by the public security body to maintain its 
abilities, preparedness, and the level of performance of the 
officers, noncommissioned officers, and soldiers--something 
highlighted during recent incidents on a level that calls for 
pride. 
  Al-'Adwan said that the prime minister expressed his 
confidence in and admiration of the level reached by the public 
security body. He said he is fully reassured about its ability 
to fully carry out its tasks. 

