Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Brigadier 'Abd-al-Rahim Muhammad 
Husayn, said after his meeting with His Excellency the 
ambassador of the Kingdom of Morocco in Khartoum yesterday that 
the accused Muhammad 'Abd-al-Rahman al-Halifi, who participated 
in the attack on worshippers in the al-Thawrah Mosque in the 
first quarter in Omdurman is not a Moroccan. He said 
investigations had indicated him to be of Najdi origin and that 
his family had emigrated in the 1920's to Tunisia and now 
resided in Libya. The minister said the accused had confessed 
participating in the hideous incident together with his 
colleagues. The minister said those named during the 
investigations were now being interrogated. 

