<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns UN Human Rights Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1302165394 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 2245 GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1302165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sudan has said that paragraphs occurring in the 
report of Gaspard Biru, who is the special rapporteur on human 
rights in Sudan, represent a deliberate insult to the Islamic 
religion, and they make it necessary to interrogate the author 
of the report and be condemned by all states, authorities and 
organizations, which respect the rights of man and humanity. 
This is because of the insult against Islam included in the 
report. 
  In a statement issued yesterday by the Foreign Ministry in 
this connection, it strongly condemned the insult addressed by 
the rapporteur against the Islamic religion and its beliefs. 
The Foreign Ministry demanded the ommission of the paragraphs 
from the report touching on this matter. The statement pointed 
out that Biru's report is part of a bigger plot targeting the 
Islamic religion and its beliefs. 

</TEXT>

