<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Transport Minister Arrives, Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1402174294 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1635 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1402174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 14 Feb (INA) -- Iraqi Transport and 
Communications Minister Dr. Ahmad Murtada Ahmad Khalil, arrived 
here today within the context of a trade protocol Iraq and Sudan 
have signed in the field of transportation. 
  In a statement to the INA correspondent in Khartoum, Dr. 
Ahmad Murtada Ahmad Khalil said his four-day visit to Sudan 
seeks to promote constant bilateral cooperation in the field of 
transportation, to discuss the exchange of expertise, and to 
encourage visits by officials from both countries so they may 
learn about the potential for bilateral cooperation in this 
regard. 
  The transport and communications minister expressed Iraq's 
willingness to cooperate fully and constructively with the 
fraternal Sudanese, and to provide them with technical expertise 
in this regard to foster strong and special ties between the two 
countries -- ties that will realize the aspirations and 
ambitions of their peoples -- in order to overcome difficult 
circumstances and break the embargo imposed on Iraq. 

</TEXT>

