<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   France's Juppe Arrives for 3-Day Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Peres, Juppe Discuss Cooperation </H4>
<F P=102> TA1402092694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 14 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1402092694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Reacting to yesterday's attack against the Shin Bet 
men near Ramallah, Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres said this 
morning that Israel will take all the steps possible from the 
military and legal viewpoints to prevent attacks against Israeli 
civilians and security personnel without any relation to the 
peace talks and, at the same time, will pursue the political 
negotiations. Mr. Peres made these remarks to our political 
correspondent Shlomo Raz. 
  Minister Peres met with visiting French Foreign Minister 
Alain Juppe this morning. Following the meeting, the guest said 
that beginning next month, Israelis visiting France for short 
periods will not require visas. The two ministers also agreed 
on bilateral space research cooperation. It was also reported 
that Israel and France will tighten their political and military 
relations, especially in the research sphere. 

</TEXT>

