<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   France's Juppe Arrives for 3-Day Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Rabin, Juppe Meet </H4>
<F P=102> TA1402120094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1100 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1402120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The French defense minister is also slated to 
arrive in Israel next month. This was reported during the 
meeting between French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe and Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin a short while ago in Jerusalem. Rabin 
thanked the French minister for approving the European mandate 
for negotiations on updating the economic agreement between the 
EC and Israel. Rabin also thanked Juppe for canceling the need 
for entry visas for Israelis visiting France. 
  Our political correspondent Udi Segal reports that Rabin and 
the French foreign minister discussed developments in the peace 
talks, and Mr. Juppe disclosed that France is trying to promote 
the establishment of a television station in the territories. 
Rabin said that Israel would agree to the establishment of a 
Palestinian television station only within the context of a full 
agreement with the Palestinians on Gaza-Jericho First. 

</TEXT>

