<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   France's Juppe Arrives for 3-Day Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Juppe on NATO Ultimatum, Serbs </H4>
<F P=102> LD1402204194 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
1900 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1402204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alain Juppe, who is currently visiting Israel, 
repeated that the NATO ultimatum was not a bluff: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] The NATO decision is not bluff. It 
is a real ultimatum, and it is up to the UN Protection Force 
command to tell us when the ultimatum expires, whether the 
alliance demands -- which were drawn up in narrow consultation 
with the UN secretary- general -- are met or not. If they are 
not met, then we will have to draw the conclusions. In other 
words, we will have to destroy the artillery positions that have 
not been pulled back. If the demands are met, then all the 
best. You know, I have kept repeating -- when I was in Zagreb, 
in Sarajevo -- that there is no lasting solution other than a 
diplomatic and political one. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

